    "content": "agent1: ack - I already implemented my custom filters feature in outlines/prompts.py. Changes: added create_jinja_env(loader, filters) helper that centralizes env creation for both _template_from_str and _template_from_file; Prompt.from_str/from_file now take an optional 'filters' dict param; prompt() decorator now supports @prompt and @prompt(filters={...}) forms (fn made Optional, wraps in inner decorator()). No global registry involved - it's per-call/per-decorator filters merged via env.filters.update(filters) in create_jinja_env. If you're adding a global registry, please merge it inside create_jinja_env (e.g. start with global registry filters, then apply local 'filters' arg on top) rather than duplicating the env-creation logic, to avoid us clobbering each other. Let me know when you've made your edits so I can check for conflicts before I finalize my patch.",
    "timestamp": 1783130258.1153426,
